provisions.content:
12. The funds and resources of the Authority shall consist of-                  Funds and
                                                                                   resources of
            such sums as may be provided by Parliament for the Authority in        the Authority.
            the Estimates of Revenue and Expenditure;
            such sums as may be allocated from time to time to the Authority
            from loan funds;
            moneys earned or arising from any property, investments, mortgages
            and debentures acquired by or vested in the Authority;
            any property, mortgages, debentures, or investments acquired by
            or vested in the Authority;
            sums borrowed by the Authority for the purpose of meeting any of
            its obligations or discharging any of its functions;
            revenues from charges imposed by the Authority for use of any
            facility or services provided by it;
            all other sums or property which may in any manner become payable
            to or vested in the Authority in respect of any matter incidental to
            its powers and duties.
